{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The TK model encodes queries and documents independently by using a small number of transformer layers (up to three) before kernel pooling to obtain an optimal ratio between effectiveness and efficiency.",
    "Hofstätter et al.",
    "also proposed the TK model with local attention (TKL) [107], which uses local self-attention rather than the self-attention of the encoder of the transformer to perform pooling over windows of document terms via a modified KNRM.The above-mentioned pretrained language models require different training and fine-tuning phases to adapt to different tasks.",
    "By contrast, Raffel et al.",
    "introduced a unified architecture, T5 (text-to-text transfer transformer) [25],that converts all NLP tasks into text-to-text tasks."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "also proposed the TK model with local attention (TKL) [107], which uses local self-attention rather than the self-attention of the encoder of the transformer to perform pooling over windows of document terms via a modified KNRM.The above-mentioned pretrained language models require different training and fine-tuning phases to adapt to different tasks.",
    "introduced a unified architecture, T5 (text-to-text transfer transformer) [25],that converts all NLP tasks into text-to-text tasks."
